jmf.language

Class JavaModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • jmf.module.AbstractModule
      • jmf.language.JavaModule

  • public class JavaModule
extends AbstractModule
    Testmodule-class of the interoperability test that is used at Java-side JavaModules are started from the Java-side within the interoperability test between Java and C++. They are kept simple and only contain functionality that is necessary for the test, such as subscribe or publish, send a request, set an additional state or check if their registry contains a peer with certain properties.
    Author:
    Matthias Blohm Date created on 10/9/15.
